                            <ab>
                                <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Thanatos"><name nymRef="#Θάνατος">Θάνατ<unclear>ος</unclear></name></persName>
                            </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
               
                <p/>              
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Thanatos <supplied reason="explanation">la Mort</supplied>.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Thanatos <supplied reason="explanation">Death</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Thanatos <supplied reason="explanation">la Morte</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The inscription mentions the genie of death, which was probably the figure painted next to it.</p>
                <p>For the tomb, see <bibl><ptr target="#thorn2006"/>, p. <citedRange>342</citedRange> and fig. 217</bibl>.</p>
            </div></body>
